### Rationale

| Criterion | Recursive | Iterative |
|-----------|-----------|-----------|
| **Clarity** | Mirrors BST logic naturally; easier to understand | Requires explicit stack management; more verbose |
| **Maintenance** | Simpler code, fewer bugs in core logic | More state to track; higher cognitive load |
| **Space (best case)** | O(log n) call stack for balanced BST | O(log n) explicit stack |
| **Space (worst case)** | O(n) call stack for skewed BST | O(n) explicit stack |
| **Stack overflow risk** | Yes, on highly skewed trees | No (controlled by explicit stack) |
| **Real-world BSTs** | Usually balanced (AVL/RB); recursion safe | Necessary for production systems with unpredictable data |

